success: true
exit_code: 0
----- stdout -----
Render a note to a document artifact.

`--to` selects the output format: `pdf` (the default) or `typst`, the emitted Typst document. The `pdf` format shells out to pandoc and typst, so both must be on `PATH`; the `typst` format needs no external tool.

Usage: ntropy render [OPTIONS] [ID|QUERY]...

Arguments:
  [ID|QUERY]...
          A full ULID or a query DSL expression (joined from trailing arguments; omitted = choose from all notes)

Options:
      --to <FORMAT>
          The output format: `pdf` (default) or `typst`
          
          [default: pdf]

      --vault <PATH>
          Operate on the vault at this path (overrides all other resolution)

      --engine <NAME>
          Override the format's default engine (`pdf`'s default is `pandoc`)

  -n, --non-interactive
          Force non-interactive (plain) behavior even on a TTY

  -o, --output <PATH>
          Write the artifact here instead of `./<slug>.<ext>`

      --strict
          Treat malformed/badly-named notes as errors instead of warnings

  -p, --print
          Print the artifact's path to stdout on success

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

----- stderr -----
